<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-01T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-01T18:00:00-05:00" n="941" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d941">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102S/2553a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-01T18:00:00-05:00">November
                                    1, 1941—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>915. In order that the Department may be able to give full weight to
                            local conditions at Shanghai in connection with problems relating to the
                            Shanghai area, the Department desires that you report in a confidential
                            telegram your views in regard to the local situation at present,
                            including the question of any danger of attempted forceful encroachment
                            from any source upon the International Settlement.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>